=== CGI MANAGEMENT (DYNAMIC SCRIPT EXECUTION) ===
    ‚òê Define a `cgi-bin/` folder for scripts
    ‚òê Execute a Python script (`.py`) as CGI
    ‚òê Execute a PHP (`.php`) script as CGI
    ‚òê Capture script output and send it as a response
    ‚òê Test with a simple `Python` script:
        @python [
            # cgi-bin/test.py
            print("Content-Type: text/html\n")
            print("<h1>Hello from Python CGI</h1>")
        ]
    ‚òê Test with a simple `PHP` script:
        @php [
            <!-- cgi-bin/test.php -->
            <?php echo "<h1>Hello from PHP CGI</h1>"; ?>
        ]
